    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what it means — tracing the author's intent within the canonical context of ancient Israel's covenant theology, the Psalter's editorial logic, and the New Testament's reappropriation of this psalm's protest. The movements below follow the psalm's four-part argument. Where the original Hebrew sharpens an English word, a brief note supplements the exposition.",
